summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of computer brands based on their share within a survey sample and their repeat purchase percentage. Dell leads with the largest share of the survey sample at 26%, also exhibiting a high repeat purchase rate of 67%. HP/Compaq follows with 23% of the sample and a 47% repeat rate. Apple holds 10% of the sample with a 36% repeat rate. Toshiba and Gateway represent smaller sample shares of 6% and 4% respectively, with repeat rates of 19% and 58%. IBM/Lenovo has the smallest sample share at 2% and a repeat rate of 29%. The structure is comparative, highlighting market presence and customer loyalty across different brands.
